<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">In 18 months of playing, I have never heard of, or been declined a group based on hybrid exp penalty. If this was the case, you would have to balance your group accordingly. A group of 53's (including hybrids) would lose exp to a 56 warrior.<p>

Lately, I have noticed occasional groups looking for a 'Taunter'. Monks Rogues and to a degree Warriors, have a natural taunt w/ their weapons, yes.  Unfortunately, when a sup/CH or 1000dd screams out from a caster (and it always does), this fact can be null and void.<br>
Taunting with the taunt key can be done. However, takes the warrior the time to run to the mob, press it and hope that it works.  Added by the fact, the caster is running around hoping it aggroes to the warrior. That's annoying as any taunter knows.<p>

Paladins on the other hand, see the aggro'ed mob move to the caster, press the hotkeyed 'stun' w/o moving themselves, frees the caster and runs over to attack (stun is an incredibly powerful taunt).  also, it costs little mana, casts very fast and at 52 (49, 2) 3 seperate stuns are in a paladins arsenal.  <p>

In Karnors, when a dd caster begins to cast, i stun the mob. Allowing our wizzies,druids,mages and such to blast at will while the mob is frozen 90% of the time.<br>
Very little damage is taken by the tanks at the cost of a little blue bar (mana).<br>
How a warrior surpasses or even matches this feat is unknown to me.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
