<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Paladins should get better 1HS without a doubt. Well we can only carry one of em. And as for a shield, I wish Verant would maybe up the bonuses for having a shield. I mean the 10-15 AC most pallies get using a shield before levels 46+ when you can get/afford the AC 25 ones does not really make that much of a difference up considering the better warrior armor. Maybe a block skill for pallies using a shields should be implemented. <p>

And as for flaming swords... Oh give it a rest! SoulFire is a very detailed quest and you will need friends to help you. And after you get it you never use it in a fight as it is just too slow. It just looks cool, impresses people, and lets people know you're a paladin who worked hard to get it and deserves it. Hell Mithril 2HS and a TBB are much better than SoulFire and FBSS. Good luck getting an FBBS before 40. All it is is just one step closer to the Fiery Avenger and the epic quest(2HS) Fiery Defender. But after you get the FA its not that hard to get FD. I wish Verant got rid of the quest items you could make from the Dragon Scales that drop off of Naggy and Vox that we need for FA so ####### farmers can't make the Dragon BP and Dragonscale Cloak to Ebay. But as for whining warriors, you know have something to look forward to as well. Your epic quest sword has black and red lightning around it! Thats cool enough. Hehe even though flames are much cooler you should now stop whining.<p>

But as for "pure" tanking duties we are inadequate. Warriors do more damage thus more taunt factor and can also soak up that damage better but that doesnt mean we flat out suck. We are in the number two spot as we should be. However, the other duty of a tank besides soaking up damage is keeping the MOB on you. Warriors are okay at this but we are better. Like Steak said our stuns keep the MOB helpless. In addition to that we can also park MOBs when a pull goes bad and monk can't split it or FD fails for whatever reason. Someone pulls 3 nasty SOB MOBs in Karnor's the Warrior is either gonna be beaten to sh*ts and everyone will have to zone or the pally can step in, root them and keep them rooted (most high level classes that do get root do not keep it memmed while we should and do) while the rest of the group concentrates on one MOB at a time. Trust me there are not that many better feelings in EQ when the whole group says "Boy I sure am glad we had a pally". <p>

If there is anything that makes me mad at Verant its the new UBER warrior armor. Sure our Deepwater has nice AC and spells but the warrior items have spells they NEVER get! I'll take some brand new newbie spells that I never get such as Invisibility than old recycled ones I already have with a half-day casting time any day! <p>

And as for the dude who was wondering about the 125% exp penalty from the party. Its true! Everyone in the group levels slower when hybrids are there. We suffer from the exp penalty as well. Hell sometimes I think we're 50% warrior 15% cleric and 35% exp penalty.<p>

And as for the dude who soloed better with a warrior than a pally you sure are in for a long haul later on. At level 18 you're not even scratching the surface of a paladin's powers. At level 18 the warrior has most of his skills available to him while the pally does not. In the upcoming levels the pally will get better heals, buffs, and utility spells. You don't even have root yet! If you solo with a warrior you're gonna spend lots of money on bandaging and sitting on your arse waiting for HPs. Warriors are not a solo class. Well maybe post 50 when they turn UBER but not now.<p>

Best of luck everyone.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
