<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hail all,<p>

I am a paladin in my early 20s, and I am mainly concerned with 1 thing: Are groups really *that* hard to get after 50? I ask because I have finally found a class that I love, and am willing to invest the time to take him 60+.<p>

I have heard that hybrids have a harder time finding a group after 50, but even in my 20s I have heard other players say, "good, with that hybrid out of the group, we get full exp." If it only gets worse from here, I am going to be nervous lol :) BTW, I was a 22 shaman when I heard that statement.<p>

And one more thing, I have also not found official confirmation of exp penalties for hybrids. But I have heard that hybrids get a -25% exp hit, but a human gets +10%. So does that mean I have a -15% exp hit being a human paladin? Lol, something tells me that it matters very little, even at higher levels (besides in people's minds.)<p>

Thanks all and good hunting!<br>
Rotep<br>
Human Paladin<br>
Veeshan</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
